// FLUTTER PROJECT RULESET
// Applies to: *.dart, pubspec.yaml, analysis_options.yaml

// ⚙️ GENERAL RULES
- Follow Dart and Flutter's official style guide (https://dart.dev/guides/language/effective-dart)
- Use Flutter 3.x APIs and Material 3 components
- Avoid deprecated APIs or widgets
- Always annotate overrides and nullability

// 📦 PACKAGE AND DEPENDENCY MANAGEMENT (pubspec.yaml)
- Keep dependencies up-to-date and remove unused ones
- Group related dependencies with comments (e.g., state management, UI, utilities)
- Use `flutter pub upgrade` and run `flutter pub get` after modifying
- Avoid pinned versions unless needed for compatibility
- Always validate `pubspec.yaml` syntax and indentation

// 🧱 ARCHITECTURE
- Prefer Clean Architecture: separate data, domain, and presentation
- Structure app by feature, not by layer (feature-first organization)
- For state management, prefer BLoC or Riverpod (based on team standard)
- Keep widgets lean: UI-only logic in widgets, business logic in blocs/usecases

// 🧪 TESTING
- Every use case should have a unit test
- Avoid UI logic in widgets to allow proper widget testing
- Prefer `golden tests` for visual consistency when applicable
- Ensure bloc and service logic are covered

// 📄 NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Widget files: `<name>_widget.dart`
- Page files: `<feature>_page.dart`
- Bloc: `<feature>_bloc.dart`, state, event
- Use snake_case for files and PascalCase for classes
- Avoid abbreviations unless widely known (e.g., UI, API)

// 💬 LOCALIZATION
- Use `flutter gen-l10n` or `intl` for localization
- Avoid hardcoded strings in UI
- Keep `l10n.yaml` up-to-date if structure changes

// 🖼️ ASSETS AND THEMING
- Register all image assets and fonts in `pubspec.yaml`
- Use theme extensions and avoid inline styles
- Apply responsive layouts using MediaQuery or LayoutBuilder

// 🚀 PERFORMANCE
- Use const constructors when possible
- Avoid rebuilding expensive widgets unnecessarily
- Cache network images and heavy resources
- Use Flutter DevTools to profile app performance

// ⚠️ AUTO-GENERATED FILES
- Never manually edit `.g.dart`, `.freezed.dart`, or `.mocks.dart`
- Ensure generators like build_runner and freezed are configured in pubspec
- Regenerate after model or annotation changes

